ferc_filing_data.tariff_title: New Hope Power Partnership FERC Electric Tariff

record_data.record_plain_text: NEW HOPE POWER PARTNERSHIP FERC ELECTRIC TARIFF 1. Availability: New Hope Power Partnership ( New Hope ) makes electric energy and capacity available under this Tariff to any purchaser for resale. 2. Applicability: This Tariff is applicable to all sales of electric energy or capacity by New Hope not otherwise subject to a particular rate schedule or contract of New Hope. 3. Rates: All sales shall be made at rates established by agreement between the purchaser and New Hope. 4. Reassignment of Transmission Capacity: New Hope may reassign transmission capacity that it has reserved for its own use at a price not to exceed the highest of: (1) the original transmission rate paid by New Hope; (2) the applicable transmission provider s maximum stated firm transmission rate on file at the time of the transmission reassignment; or (3) New Hope s own opportunity costs, capped at the applicable transmission provider s cost of expansion at the time of the sale to the eligible customer. New Hope will not recover opportunity costs in connection with reassignments without making a separate filing under Section 205. Except for the price, the terms and conditions under which the reassignment is made shall be the terms and conditions governing the original grant by the transmission provider. New Hope may only reassign transmission capacity to a customer eligible to take service under the transmission provider s open access transmission tariff or other transmission rate schedules. New Hope will report the name(s) of any such assignee(s) in its quarterly reports. 5. Other Terms and Conditions: All other terms and conditions shall be established by agreement between the purchaser and New Hope. 6. Certain Affiliate Transactions Prohibited: No sale may be made pursuant to this Tariff to any public utility with a franchised electric service territory that is controlled by, under common control with, or controlling, New Hope. 7. Change in Status Reporting Requirement: New Hope must timely report to the Commission any change in status that would reflect a departure from the characteristics the Commission relied upon in granting market-based rate authority. A change in status includes, but is not limited to, each of the following: (i) ownership of control of generation or transmission facilities or inputs to electric power production other than fuel supplies, or (ii) affiliation with any entity not disclosed in the application for market-based rate authority that owns or controls generation or transmission facilities or inputs to electric power production, or affiliation with any entity that has a franchised service area. Any change in status must be filed no later than 30 days after the change in status occurs. 8. Effective Date: This tariff is effective as of the date provided by the Commission.
